                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370227-886-offence-1 t18370227-name-1264"></join>Henry Trowse Stevenson</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370227-name-1265" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1265" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1265" type="surname" value="STEVENSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1265" type="given" value="HENRY TROWSE"></interp>HENRY TROWSE STEVENSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a labourer in the St. Katharine's Docks, and live in Pell-street, St. George's. The prisoner was brought to sleep with a fellow-lodger, in another bed in the same room—I missed my shirt on Tuesday night, the 7th of February.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370227-name-1266" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1266" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1266" type="surname" value="MACKSEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1266" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES MACKSEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a stone-mason. The prisoner slept with me on the night the shirt was lost—the prosecutor slept in another bed—he and I got up, and went to work about half-past six o'clock, and left the prisoner in bed.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370227-name-1267" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1267" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1267" type="surname" value="FORD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1267" type="given" value="WIILIAM"></interp>WIILIAM FORD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a private in the Marines at Woolwich—the prisoner is the same. On the 10th of February, he came into the room where I was stopping, and asked who slept in the bed by the side of the cupboard—I said, "No one"—he said, "There is a shirt at that bed; I want you to stow it away in your bag"—I said I would—when he was gone, I told the corporal I believed it was stolen.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370227-name-1268" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1268" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1268" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1268" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS TAYLOR</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a colour-sergeant in the Marines. I took the shirt from the bed—I represented this to the officer, and went before the Magistrate.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370227-name-1269" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1269" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1269" type="surname" value="DAVIES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1269" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM DAVIES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a constable. I took the prisoner, and accused him of robbing a person of a shirt—he said he knew nothing about it—I fond 5<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. on him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370227-name-1270" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1270" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1270" type="surname" value="STEVENSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370227-name-1270" type="given" value="HENRY TROWSE"></interp>HENRY TROWSE STEVENSON</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I lost this shirt off a shelf—there was no other left in the room—the prisoner never undressed himself at all—he slept with his clothes on.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I met some comrades—we got drinking for some time—I was taken to some lodgings—I do not know where, being stupefied</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183702270190"></xptr>
               <p>with drink—having been in the habit of pulling off my shirt at night, I, in my hurry next morning, put on one, not knowing whether it was mine or not.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
